news/article/article.aspx?aid=3026524|title=Lotte Duty Free to release a web drama|date=23 November 2016|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Music video===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|- \n! Year\n! Title\n! Singer\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2009 || \"Kiss\" || [[Sandara Park]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.joins.com/article/3762106|title=\uc774\ubbfc\ud638\u00b7\uc0b0\ub2e4\ub77c\ubc15 \"\ud0a4\uc2a4 100\ubc88 \uc785\uc220 \ud241\ud241\" CF\ud0a4\uc2a4\uc2e0 \ud654\uc81c|date=6 September 2009|website=JoongAng Ilbo|language=ko}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Lee Min-ho discography}}\n\n* ''My Everything'' (2013, Korean)\n* ''My Everything'' (2013, Japanese)\n* ''Song For You'' (2014)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Lee Min-ho}}\n\n==Others==\n[[File:\ubc30\uc6b0 \uc774\ubbfc\ud638 \ucc38\uc11d \ud398\ub808\ub85c \ub85c\uc250 \ud06c\ub9ac\uc2a4\ub9c8\uc2a4 \uc774\ubca4\ud2b8 \ud604\uc7a5.jpg|thumb|upright|In December 2015]]\n\n===Ambassador roles===\n* Honorary Ambassador for UNICEF's Love Net campaign to fight malaria (2009\u20132010)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010112407455172262|script-title=ko:\ubc30\uc6b0 \uc774\ubbfc\ud638, '\ud3ed\ub825 \ucd94\ubc29 \ucea0\ud398\uc778' \ud2b8\uc704\ud130\ub85c \uc55e\uc7a5\uc11c\ub2e4|date=24 November 2010|website=Asia Economy |language=ko}}</ref>\n* PR Ambassador for Konkuk University (2010)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201006031605281001|script-title=ko:\u2018\ub450\ubbfc\ud638\u2019 \uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \ubbfc\ud638-\uc774\ubbfc\ud638, \uac74\uad6d\ub300 \ud64d\ubcf4\ub300\uc0ac \ub098\ub780\ud788 \uc704\ucd09|date=3 June 2010|website=Newsen|language=ko}}</ref>\n* Honorary Prosecutor or basically a PR ambassador for Korean Prosecutor (2012)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2946604|title=Actors named celebrity prosecutors|date=4 January 2012|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\n* PR ambassador for the Chilean campaign \"Reforestemos Patagonia\" organized by Minoz Chile (2013)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=011&aid=0002409139|script-title=ko:\uc774\ubbfc\ud638 '\ud30c\ud0c0\uace0\ub2c8\uc544 \uc7ac\uc2dd\ub9bc \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8' \ub3d9\ucc38 \"\uc232 \uc0b4\ub9ac\uc790\"|date=17 October 2013|website=Seoul Economic Daily|language=ko}}</ref> \n* Public Ambassador for 'Korean Tourism Campaign', also called as 'The Face of Korean Tourism' (July 28, 2015)<ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho to promote Korea\u2019s tourism|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201507281141398323408_2|website=[[The Korea Herald|Kpop Herald]]|date=28 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho Promotes Korea Tourism|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/07/31/2015073100563.html|website=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|date=31 July 2015}}</ref>\n* Honorary Ambassador for the '2018 Pyeongchang Winter Olympics' (September 25, 2015)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/search1/2603000000.html?cid=AEN20150925005100315|title=Actor Lee Min-ho named goodwill ambassador for 2018 PyeongChang Winter Games|website=[[Yonhap News Agency]]|date=25 September 2015}}</ref>\n* PR Ambassador for Visit Korea Year 2016\u20132018 (November 7, 2015)<ref>{{cite web|title=\uc774\ubbfc\ud638-AOA \uc124\ud604, '\ud55c\uad6d\ubc29\ubb38\uc758 \ud574' \ud64d\ubcf4\ub300\uc0ac \uc704\ucd09|url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201511070100073380004569&servicedate=20151106|website=Sports Chosun|date=6 November 2015|language=Korean}}</ref>\n* Honorary Ambassador for the King Sejong Institute Foundation (KSIF)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=3065017|title=Lee Min-ho named ambassador|date=3 July 2019|website=Korea JoongAng Daily|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Philanthropy===\nIn 2014, Lee set up the PROMIZ website, a fund-raising platform to raise awareness and encourage donation for social and humanitarian causes.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\uc774\ubbfc\ud638, \uae30\ubd80\ud50c\ub7ab\ud3fc \u2018\ud504\ub85c\ubbf8\uc988\u2019 \uc624\ud508, \uc0ac\ud68c\uacf5\ud5cc \uc2dc\uc791|language=Korean|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201406131452191210|website=Newsen|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Min-jin|title=Lee Min-ho gives gifts to staff to celebrate his birthday|url=http://khnews.kheraldm.com/view.php?ud=20140624000885&md=20140704143221_BK|website=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref> Proceeds from the sale of PROMIZ merchandise are given to the selected partners to execute the charity projects. The site has since raised US$50,000 from him and his fans to help create wells in Malawi through non-profit organisation [[Charity: Water]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Jong-chan|title=Hallyu star Lee Min-ho and his fans donate $50,000 to help dig wells in Africa|url=http://eng.ajunews.com/view/20140930151851357|website=AJU Business Daily|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=PMZ(Lee minho x MINOZ)|url=https://my.charitywater.org/leeminho|website=Charity: Water|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref> It has also raised funds and contributed donations to several causes;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3030172|title=Lee Min-ho\u2019s Promiz makes major donation|date=23 February 2017|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref> such as World Water Day, the \"Transparent Umbrella Project\" and the \"Making Warm Winter for Both Bodies and Hearts\" campaign.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho Donates W50 Million to Mark World Water Day|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2016/03/23/2016032301304.html|date=23 March 2016|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho to hand out transparent umbrellas to children|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201608121756510377869_2|date=12 August 2016|work=[[The Korea Herald|Kpop Herald]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho donates $44,000 to victims of child abuse|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201702231717187959471_2|date=23 February 2017|work=[[The Korea Herald|Kpop Herald]]}}</ref> In 2016, PROMIZ won the Korea Good Brand Awards.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho\u2019s Promiz wins Korea Good Brand Awards|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201605261319112153282_2|date=26 May 2016|work=[[The Korea Herald|Kpop Herald]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Lee donated 100 million [[South Korean won|won]] to [[UNICEF]] to aid victims of a devastating earthquake in Nepal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/05/06/2015050601425.html|title=Lee Min-ho Gives W100 Million to Nepal Recovery Effort|date=6 May 2015|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]}}</ref> In 2016, Lee was awarded by the Ministry of Health and Welfare for his contribution to society.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3020290|title=Lee Min-ho recognized for charity|date=22 June 2016|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\n\nTo mark the 10th anniversary since his debut, Lee's fans participated in several charitable causes. Lee's Chinese fans planted 510 trees in Inner Mongolia, while his Mexican fans donated to children stricken with cancer with proceeds earned from selling plastic bottle caps to recycling companies. Taiwanese and Hong Kong fans also made donations to profit organizations [[World Vision International|World Vision]] and UNICEF. The previous years, his Chile fan club donated to the humanitarian organization Patagonia Compassion; and also participated in several other charitable causes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2016/05/11/0200000000AEN20160511004000315.html|title=Global fans celebrate Lee Min-ho's debut anniversary|date=11 May 2016|work=[[Yonhap News Agency]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.asiaone.com/news/showbiz/lee-min-ho-fans-pitch-charity|title=Lee Min-ho fans pitch in for charity|date=4 April 2015|work=AsiaOne}}</ref>\n\n===Media influence===\nAs of June 2018, Lee has 3 million followers on [[Twitter]], 29 million and 17.4 million fans on [[Sina Weibo|Weibo]] and [[Facebook]] respectively.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\ub728\uac70\uc6b4 \u4e2d \ud55c\ub958 \uc5f4\ud48d\u2026\uc6e8\uc774\ubcf4\ub85c \uc0b4\ud3b4\ubcf8 \uc778\uae30\uc21c\uc704|url=http://star.mbn.co.kr/view.php?year=2014&no=1054233|website=[[Maeil Broadcasting Network]]|accessdate=25 October 2014|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title='Who rules on SNS?' : Korean celebrities with most followers|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140722000978|website=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=4 August 2014|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Chung|first1=Hyun-chae|title=Hallyu goes viral through social media|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2013/10/386_143754.html|website=[[The Korea Times]]|date=4 October 2013|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref> In 2014 and 2015, Lee topped an online poll organised by a Chinese entertainment magazine to be crowned as the \"Asian Male God\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hicap|first1=Jonathan M.|title=Lee Min Ho voted No. 1 'Asian Male God' in China|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/lee-min-ho-voted-no-1-asian-male-god-in-china/|website=[[Manila Bulletin]]|date=8 April 2014|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|script-title=zh:2014\u5e74\u5ea6\u4e9a\u6d32\u7537\u795e|language=Chinese|url=http://nanshen.ddyule.cn/|work=\u5f53\u4ee3\u5a31\u4e50\u5468\u520a|accessdate=25 October 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713193113/http://nanshen.ddyule.cn/|archivedate=July 13, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Yip|first1=Wai Yee|title=Lee Min Ho mans up|url=http://news.asiaone.com/news/showbiz/lee-min-ho-mans|website=[[The Straits Times]]|date=1 October 2014|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref> In 2017, Lee was chosen as the \"Most Favored Korean Actor\" by fans of the Korean Wave in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/park-shin-hye-lee-min-ho-top-korean-stars-in-the-us|title=Park Shin Hye, Lee Min Ho top Korean stars in the US|date=9 March 2017|work=[[The Straits Times]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Lee Min-ho}}\n* [http://www.leeminho.kr/ Official Korean website] {{in lang|ko}}\n* [http://www.minho.jp/ Official Japanese website] {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Baeksang Arts Award for Most Popular Actor}}\n{{Grand Bell Awards for Best New Actor}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lee, Min-ho}}\n[[Category:Male actors from Seoul]]\n[[Category:Actors from Seoul]]\n[[Category:South Korean male film actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male television actors]]\n[[Category:Konkuk University alumni]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean actor, singer and model}}\n{{Korean name|Lee}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Lee Min-ho\n| image              = 140120 Minho Lee c.jpg\n| caption            = Lee at the premiere of ''[[Hot Young Bloods]]'' in January 2014.\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1987|6|22}}\n| birth_place        = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| residence          = \n| nationality        = \n| other names        = \n| alma_mater         = [[Konkuk University]]\n| occupation         = {{Hlist|Actor|singer|model}}\n| height             = {{height|cm=187}}<ref>http://minoz.co.kr/page/profile.php</ref>\n| years_active       = 2003\u2013present\n| label              = [[Universal Music Group]]\n| agent              = {{ubl|MYM Entertainment|IMX Inc.|[[Huayi Brothers]]}}\n| website            = {{URL|www.leeminho.kr/}}\n| module             = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n  | hangul = {{linktext|\uc774|\ubbfc\ud638}}\n  | hanja  = {{linktext|\u674e|\u654f|\u93ac}}\n  | rr     = I Min-ho\n  | mr     = Yi Minho\n}}\n| signature          = Lee Min-ho's signature.png\n}}\n'''Lee Min-ho''' ({{korean|\uc774\ubbfc\ud638|\u674e\u654f\u93ac}}, born June 22, 1987)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/korean_Lee_Min-ho.php|title=Lee Min-ho (\uc774\ubbfc\ud638, Korean actor) @ HanCinema :: The Korean Movie & Drama Database|website=HanCinema|accessdate=August 18, 2018}}</ref> is a South Korean actor, singer,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2009102120505396430|title=[10LINE] Lee Min-ho|date=21 October 2009|website=10Asia}}</ref> and model.<ref>https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2015/08/386_185596.html</ref><ref>https://www.cosmo.ph/entertainment/lee-min-ho-facts-movies-shows-a2520-20180911-lfrm</ref><ref>https://channels.vlive.tv/C7A6F1/vtoday/0.11956032</ref> He gained widespread fame in Korea and some parts of Asia with his role as Gu Jun-pyo in ''[[Boys Over Flowers (TV series)|Boys Over Flowers]]'' in 2009. The role won him a Best New Actor award at the 45th [[Baeksang Arts Awards]]. His notable lead roles in television series include ''[[City Hunter (TV series)|City Hunter]]'' (2011), ''[[The Heirs]]'' (2013) and ''[[Legend of the Blue Sea]]'' (2016). The success of Lee's television series in Asia established him as a top [[Korean Wave|Hallyu]] star. Apart from his television career, Lee featured in the first lead role in the film ''[[Gangnam Blues]]'' (2015), followed by his first China-produced film ''[[Bounty Hunters (2016 film)|Bounty Hunters]]'' (2016).\n\n==Early life and education==\nLee was born in [[Heukseok-dong]], [[Dongjak-gu]], [[Seoul]]. As a child, Lee had hoped to become a professional football player. He was selected for the youth football class of South Korean manager and former professional player [[Cha Bum-Kun]], but an injury during his 5th grade of elementary school put an end to this aspiration.<ref name=\"life graph\">{{cite web|title=Life graph of Lee Min Ho, \"Actor's job is to give hope and courage\"|url=http://m.star.naver.com/minho/news/end?id=2150310|work=[[Naver Corporation|Naver]]|accessdate=14 July 2014}}</ref> In his second year of high school, Lee turned to acting.\n\nHe majors in Film & Art at [[Konkuk University]].<ref name=\"life graph\" />\n\n==Career==\n===2006\u20132008: Beginnings===\nLee started auditioning and landed minor roles in several television dramas such as ''[[Nonstop (TV series)|Nonstop 5]]'' and ''Recipe of Love''. His official debut role was in an EBS series, ''Secret Campus'' (2003).<ref name=interview1>{{cite web|title=Star Diary: Lee Min-ho \u2013 Part 1|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?sec=ent5&idxno=2010042609182320330|work=10Asia|accessdate=28 October 2014}}</ref> Early in his career, Lee went by the stage name ''Lee Min'' because his agency thought his birth name was too ordinary. However, as his stage name was pronounced and written ([[Hangul]]) in the same way as the Korean word ''imin'', which means \"immigration\", he later said it was difficult to find himself in internet search results. He eventually went back to using his original name.<ref name=\"interview3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?sec=ent5&idxno=2010042808580745367|title=Star Diary: Lee Min-ho \u2013 Part 3|work=10Asia|accessdate=28 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, his acting career was put on hold for a year following a serious car accident, while riding with fellow actor [[Jung Il-woo]]. Lee was severely injured and spent several months bedridden.<ref name=\"life graph\" /> Upon recovery, Lee received his first leading role in the high-school drama ''[[Mackerel Run]]'' in 2007, but the series was reduced to only eight episodes due to low viewership ratings.<ref name=interview2>{{cite web|title=Star Diary: Lee Min-ho \u2013 Part 2|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010042709004335516|work=10Asia|accessdate=14 July 2014}}</ref> In 2008, he appeared in various roles on television (dramas ''[[Get Up (2008 film)|Get Up]]'' and ''[[I Am Sam (TV series)|I Am Sam]]'') and two movies, ''[[Public Enemy Returns]]'' and ''[[Our School's E.T.]]''. During the shooting of the latter, he became good friends with [[Kim Su-ro|actor Kim Su-ro]], who later praised him on a variety show: \"I recognize a star when I see one. When I was doing ''[[Our School's E.T.]]'', I knew that Lee Min-ho would become one of the top actors in the country\".<ref name=interview4>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010042909434654070|title=Star Diary: Lee Min-ho \u2013 Part 4|website=10Asia|accessdate=28 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132012: Breakthrough===\n[[File:Lee Min Ho crop.JPG|thumb|upright|In December 2012]]\nLee's breakthrough came in 2009 with the lead role of Gu Jun-pyo in [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]'s ''[[Boys Before Flowers (TV series)|Boys Over Flowers]]'', the Korean adaptation of the popular [[Sh\u014djo manga]] [[Boys Over Flowers|of the same name]]. Competition for the leading role was very intense and Lee only got to know he was cast from the newspapers.<ref name=\"interview5\">{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010043008554966117|title=Star Diary: Lee Min-ho \u2013 Part 5|work=10Asia|accessdate=28 October 2014}}</ref> The series attracted high viewership ratings and buzz throughout South Korea during its broadcast,<ref name=bof>{{cite web|author=Yoo Bo-lam|title=Boys Over Flowers explodes in popularity|url=http://nwww.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20090311000031|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=18 February 2013|date=11 March 2009}}</ref> Lee's new-found popularity gained him many endorsement deals and created another [[Korean Wave]] throughout Asia which made Lee a [[Hallyu]] star.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:'\uc774\ubbfc\ud638\ub97c \uc7a1\uc544\ub77c'...'\uaf43\ub0a8' \uc778\uae30\uc5d0 \uad11\uace0 \uc785\ub3c4\uc120\ub9e4 \uacbd\uc7c1|url=http://starin.edaily.co.kr/news/NewsRead.edy?SCD=EA31&newsid=01197206589556080&DCD=A10102|language=Korean|work=E Daily|date=9 January 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Star Diary: Lee Min-ho \u2013 Part 9|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010050709070149777|work=10Asia|accessdate=28 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Lee starred in romantic comedy ''[[Personal Taste]]'', in which he played an ambitious perfectionist young architect who poses as a gay man to become roommates with a young woman, leading to romantic complications. When asked about why he chose the role during an interview, he responded \"I think I would do a better job playing heavy and more defined roles when I am older. I think \"Personal Taste\" was perfect because it is bright, cheerful but you can also laugh and cry over it as well.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tenasia.co.kr/?construct=newContent&fz=news&gisaNo=2010032612460518731|title=Son Ye-jin says relieved Lee Min-ho \"not young-looking\"|work=10Asia|accessdate=28 July 2013|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130218205315/http://www.tenasia.co.kr/?construct=newContent&fz=news&gisaNo=2010032612460518731|archivedate=18 February 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, he played the titular character in action drama ''[[City Hunter (TV series)|City Hunter]]'', which was loosely based on [[Tsukasa Hojo]]'s popular [[City Hunter|manga]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?sec=ent5&idxno=2011081219122782502|title=Lee Min-ho - \"I want to find a drama where I can find myself\" |date=12 August 2011|website=10Asia}}</ref> The drama was a commercial success<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hancinema.net/sold-out-guy-lee-min-ho--30645.html|title=Sold out guy Lee Min-ho|website=Hancinema|publisher=[[Nate (web portal)|Nate]]|accessdate=14 June 2011}}</ref> across Asia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2016/01/386_196469.html|title=Actor Lee Min-ho mesmerizes Japan|work=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=8 March 2017}}</ref> and contributed to Lee's growing popularity, most notably in Japan, Philippines, China,<ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho still wanted in Japan|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2952940|work=[[JoongAng Ilbo#Korea JoongAng Daily|Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=15 July 2014 |date=17 May 2012|last1=Sunwoo|first1=Carla}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Esteves|first1=Patricia|title=Lee Min Ho: Coming to Phl doesn\u2019t feel like work|url=http://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2012/11/18/867922/lee-min-ho-coming-phl-doesn%E2%80%99t-feel-work|work=[[The Philippine Star]]|date=18 November 2012|accessdate=15 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article/22426/lee-min-ho-didnt-know-how-popular-he-was-in-china|title=Lee Min Ho Says He Was Surprised By Drama\u2019s Popularity in China|website=enewsWorld|date=2 December 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170730120106/http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article/22426/lee-min-ho-didnt-know-how-popular-he-was-in-china|archivedate=30 July 2017}}</ref> and parts of Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/3114/lee-min-ho-is-the-best-korean-actor-in-france|title=Lee Min Ho is the \u2032Best Korean Actor\u2032 in France|work=enewsWorld|date=1 February 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141216073354/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/3114/lee-min-ho-is-the-best-korean-actor-in-france|archivedate=16 December 2014}}</ref> He participated in a popular Chinese variety show ''[[Happy Camp (variety show)|Happy Camp]]'' in December 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho visits China for New Year's|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2945678|last1=Sunwoo|first1=Carla|work=[[JoongAng Ilbo#Korea JoongAng Daily|Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=16 December 2011|accessdate=5 July 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Lee starred in historical-medical drama, ''[[Faith (2012 TV series)|Faith]]'' with [[Kim Hee-sun]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kim Hee-sun, Lee Min-ho start filming|url=http://mengnews.joins.com/view.aspx?aId=2956073|work=[[JoongAng Ilbo#Korea JoongAng Daily|Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=13 July 2012}}</ref> Although the drama garnered viewership ratings around the 10% range, it was a commercial flop due to its high budget.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kim|first=Tong-hyung|title=Director of ''Hourglass'' commits suicide|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2013/07/201_139802.html|work=[[The Korea Times]]|date=23 July 2013}}</ref>\n\n===2013\u2013present: International fame===\nIn April 2013, Lee's wax figure was unveiled at the [[Madame Tussauds]] in [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/776160.shtml#.Un9G0PlLO3g |title=Lee Min-ho's wax figure unveiled at Madame Tussauds in Shanghai |work=[[Global Times]] |date=19 April 2013 |accessdate=10 November 2013}}</ref> He then released his first album \"My Everything\" in May 2013 and went on a fan meeting tour in Asia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2971978|title=Actor Lee Min-ho releases 1st album|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=23 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho adds another fan meeting|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2980269|last1=Lee|first1=Sun-min|work=[[JoongAng Ilbo#Korea JoongAng Daily|Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=12 November 2013|accessdate=2 July 2014}}</ref> \n[[File:Lee Minho LG.jpg|thumb|upright|left|In December 2013]]\nLee also announced his return to television with a new drama titled ''[[The Heirs (TV series)|The Heirs]]'', a teen drama written by [[Kim Eun-sook]].<ref name=heirs>{{cite web|last1=Oh|first1=Jean|title=Lee Min-ho, back to class|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20131008000723|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=10 October 2013|accessdate=2 July 2014}}</ref> On why he decided to take on the role of a [[chaebol]] heir in high school four years after playing one in ''[[Boys Over Flowers]]'', he answered \"Before I grew past my 20s, I wanted to play a more upbeat character, one that would allow me to return to that feeling of simple, uncomplicated innocence that I had when I was younger.\"<ref name=heirs /> Premiering on October 9, 2013, ''The Heirs'' enjoyed immense popularity both locally, with a peak rating of 28.6%, and internationally, having over one billion hits on the Chinese streaming website [[iQiyi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kdramastars.com/articles/13557/20131228/2013-kdramas-that-got-the-best-ratings.htm|title=2013 Kdramas That Got The Best Ratings|date=28 December 2013|work=KDramaStars}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Shin|first1=Kyun-jin|first2=Sung-hee|last2=Yang|title=Hallyu booming again in China, bigger than ever|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2986309|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=14 March 2013}}</ref> Lee experienced an increase in his popularity, particularly in China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2986045|title=20 million Chinese follow Lee|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=10 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimesus.com/lee-min-ho-named-no-1-korean-actor-in-china/|title=Lee Min-ho named No.1 Korean actor in China|website=[[The Korea Times]]|date=17 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2014/01/398_149690.html|title=No what-ifs to Lee Min-ho|website=The Korea Times|date=13 January 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn January 30, 2014, Lee became the first Korean celebrity to perform on China's [[CCTV New Year's Gala|CCTV Lunar New Year gala]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/china-crushes-puny-us-super-676907|title=China Crushes Puny US Super Bowl Audience: 704 Million Watch New Year Gala|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=|last=Coonan|first=Clifford|date=4 February 2014|accessdate=27 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2014/01/398_150164.html|title=Lee Min-ho invited to China TV festival|website=The Korea Times|date=20 January 2014}}</ref> He sang a song with [[Harlem Yu]], the original singer of the theme song of ''[[Meteor Garden]]'', the Taiwanese version of ''[[Hana Yori Dango (TV series)|Boys Over Flowers]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chun Wan says Lee Min-ho as 'The most wanted Actor'|url=http://english.kbs.co.kr/hallyu/entertainment_news_view.html?No=8008274|work=KBS World|accessdate=9 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\"Korean Wave\" hits Gala stage|url=http://english.cntv.cn/program/cultureexpress/20140130/101583.shtml|work=CCTV|date=30 January 2014|access-date=19 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323012530/http://english.cntv.cn/program/cultureexpress/20140130/101583.shtml|archive-date=23 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was also invited to the third conference of the South Korean Presidential Committee for Cultural Enrichment as the representative for the entertainment industry, to share and contribute to the discussion of issues related to developing Korea's cultural content.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Jin|first1=Eun-soo|title=Lee Min-ho meets President|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2987429|work=[[JoongAng Ilbo#Korea JoongAng Daily|Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=5 April 2014|accessdate=2 July 2014}}</ref> Lee received the \"Prime Minister Award\" at the 5th Korean Popular Culture & Arts Award for his contribution to Hallyu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201411111556000574880_2|title=Kim Soo-hyun, Lee Min-ho feted for spreading hallyu|website=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=11 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nLee subsequently recorded and released his second EP ''Song for You'' in October 2014 under [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music]]. As with his previous album, he stated that the tracks were recorded for his fans and that he had no ambition to pursue a singing career.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Jackson|first1=Julie|title=Lee Min-ho returning to the mic next month|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140926000708|website=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=26 September 2014|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho tops Japanese chart with second album|url=http://news.asiaone.com/news/showbiz/lee-min-ho-tops-japanese-chart-second-album|work=[[AsiaOne]]|date=13 October 2014|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref> The album release coincided with the start of his ''RE:MINHO'' fan meeting tour which spanned various Asian cities.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho plans global tour to meet fans|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2014/07/517_161397.html|website=[[The Korea Times]]|date=21 July 2014|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thousands turn out for Lee Min-ho's fan meeting in Japan|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/culturesports/2014/10/14/64/0701000000AEN20141014002800315F.html|website=[[Yonhap|Yonhap News Agency]]|date=14 October 2014|accessdate=25 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201501041744459372121_2|title=Lee Min-ho\u2019s global tour ends successfully|website=[[The Korea Herald|Kpop Herald]]|date=4 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nHe then took on a starring role [[Yoo Ha]]'s noir action film ''[[Gangnam Blues]]'' (2015), set in the 1970s when the real estate development boom swept across Gangnam area. The movie, which co-stars [[Kim Rae-won]], marks Lee's first leading role in a [[feature film]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Won|first1=Ho-Yeon|title=Lee Min-ho done with high school|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2982879|website=[[JoongAng Ilbo#Korea JoongAng Daily|Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=2 January 2014|accessdate=2 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2014/01/398_149735.html|title=`My next film project is noir'|website=The Korea Times|date=13 January 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Lee starred in the action comedy ''[[Bounty Hunters (2016 film)|Bounty Hunters]]'', directed by Shin Terra.<ref name=bounty>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/asia/bounty-hunters-lee-min-ho-to-star-1201517164/|title=Korea\u2019s Lee Min-ho Confirmed To Star in \u2018Bounty Hunters\u2019 Action Adventure|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=11 June 2015}}</ref> The film topped box office charts on its release date and went on to gross US$29 million in China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2016/07/398_208565.html|title=Lee Min-ho's 1st China movie tops sales|website=The Korea Times|date=4 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2016/07/398_209109.html|title=Lee Min-ho movie smash-hit in China|website=The Korea Times|date=11 July 2016}}</ref> Later in the year, Lee made his small-screen comeback in the fantasy romance drama ''[[Legend of the Blue Sea]]'' alongside actress [[Jun Ji-hyun]], which was a hit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/asia/gianna-jun-lee-min-ho-korean-tv-blue-sea-1201785394/|title=Gianna Jun and Lee Min-ho to Star in Korean TV Series \u2018Blue Sea\u2019|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=30 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20170126000618|title='Legend of the Blue Sea' ends strong despite being too familiar|website=The Korea Herald|date=26 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Lee was cast in the fantasy romance drama ''[[The King: Eternal Monarch]]'' written by ''[[The Heirs]]'' writer [[Kim Eun-sook]].<ref name=theking>{{cite web|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20190507003300315|title=Discharged from the military, actor Lee Min-ho cast for new drama series by star screenwriter|date=7 May 2019|website=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nLee has an elder sister, Lee Yong-jung, who is the CEO of his current agency MYM Entertainment.<ref name=\"interview3\" /><ref>{{cite web|last1=Bae |first1=Sun-young |title=Lee Min-ho, Now the Fatally Attractive Inheritor Kim Tan |url=http://www.tenasia.com/archives/74483 |website=10Asia |date=11 October 2013 |accessdate=28 October 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016023344/http://www.tenasia.com/archives/74483 |archivedate=16 October 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2016/05/398_204018.html|title=Lee Min-ho signs with sister's new agency|website=The Korea Times|date=4 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Military enlistment===\nLee Min-ho began his [[Conscription|mandatory military service]] on May 12, 2017 at Suseo Social Welfare Centre in Gangnam District Office as a public service officer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20170419000631|title=Lee Min-ho confirms May enlistment|last=Jie|first=Ye-eun|date=19 April 2017|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=20 April 2017}}</ref> Lee was unable to serve as an active duty soldier due to a car accident that took place in August 2006 with fellow actor [[Jung Il-woo]], which caused him to be bedridden for months as he had suffered serious leg injuries. He suffered another car accident in 2011 while filming ''[[City Hunter (TV series)|City Hunter]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2016/05/398_205178.html|title=Severe injuries exempt actor Lee Min-ho from active duty|website=The Korea Times|date=20 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2017/04/20/2017042001437.html|title=Lee Min-ho to Start Military Service in Gangnam Desk Job|date=20 April 2017|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|accessdate=20 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn March 15, 2018 Lee entered his military training at the Korea Army Training Centre in [[Nonsan]], [[South Chungcheong Province]]. He returned to his public service duty after four weeks of basic military training.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20180311000182|title=Actor Lee Min-ho to start army basic training|date=March 11, 2018|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=2018-03-16|author=Shim Woo-hyun}}</ref> He was discharged on April 25, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/04/26/2019042601005.html|title=Actor Lee Min-ho Completes Military Service|date=26 April 2019|website=The Chosun Ilbo}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|- \n! Year\n! Title\n! Original title\n! Role\n! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2008\n| ''[[Public Enemy Returns]]''\n| \uac15\ucca0\uc911: \uacf5\uacf5\uc758 \uc801 1-1 \n| Jung Ha-yeon\n| <ref name=interview4 /> \n|-\n| ''[[Our School's E.T.]]''\n| \uc6b8\ud559\uad50 \uc774\ud2f0 \n| Oh Sang-hoon\n| <ref name=interview4 /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.khan.co.kr/entertainment/sk_index.html?mcode=entersrs&art_id=200809042051496&sec_id=540401|script-title=ko:\u2018\uc6b8\ud559\uad50 \uc774\ud2f0\u2019 \uc774\ubbfc\ud638 \"\uc798\uc0dd\uacbc\ub2e4\uace0\uc694? \uae38\uac70\ub9ac \uce90\uc2a4\ud305 \uaf64 \ubc1b\uc558\uc8e0\"|date=4 September 2008|website=Sports Khan|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Gangnam Blues]]''\n| \uac15\ub0a8 1970\n| Kim Jong-dae\n| <ref>{{cite web|last1=Tae|first1=Sang-joon|title=LEE Min-ho Cast in YOO Ha's Action Noir|url=http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/jsp/news/news.jsp?mode=VIEW&seq=2829687|website=Korean Film Biz Zone|accessdate=8 September 2014|date=16 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Sun-min|title=Way back to Gangnam for Lee Min-ho|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2982054|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=8 September 2014|date=16 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lee Min-ho Rides Wave of Popularity to Leading Movie Role|url=ht